        "@type": "xsd:string",
        "@value": "Indictment filed 2024-09-17. 3 counts; 17 defendants on docket."
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "kb:racketeering-1-24-cr-00417-ckk-enterprise",
      "@type": [
        "uco-identity:Organization",
        "cacontology:CriminalEnterprise"
      ],
      "uco-core:name": "Social Engineering Enterprise",
      "rdfs:label": "Social Engineering Enterprise",
      "uco-core:description": {
        "@type": "xsd:string",
        "@value": "Mixed RICO enterprise under 18 U.S.C. \u00a7 1962(d) with minimum 12 co-conspirators. Role specialization: database hacker \u2014 obtain or purchase stolen crypto related databases; organizer target identifier \u2014 collate databases and prioritize high value targets; caller social engineer \u2014 cold call victims impersonating vce or email support; money launderer \u2014 convert stolen virtual currency to fiat cash or wire; residential burglar \u2014 irl break in for hardware wallet theft."
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "kb:racketeering-1-24-cr-00417-ckk-person-defendant",
      "@type": "uco-identity:Person",
      "uco-core:name": "Defendant-1",
      "rdfs:label": "Defendant-1",
      "uco-core:description": {
        "@type": "xsd:string",
        "@value": "Principal placeholder for multi-defendant RICO prosecution (17 defendants)."
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "kb:racketeering-1-24-cr-00417-ckk-fraud-conduct",
      "@type": "uco-action:Action",
      "uco-core:name": "Alleged social-engineering fraud conduct",
      "rdfs:label": "Alleged social-engineering fraud conduct",
      "uco-core:description": {
        "@type": "xsd:string",
        "@value": "Mixed coordinated virtual-currency theft via social engineering during 2023-10 to 2025-05. Mechanisms include stolen cryptocurrency databases shared as targets, unauthorized account push notifications before fraudulent calls, fraudulent support calls impersonating VCE or email providers, seed phrase and private key harvesting, cloud account intrusion to locate wallet secrets, in-real-life break-ins targeting hardware wallets, virtual currency laundering via privacy coins and offshore exchanges, unlicensed crypto-to-cash exchange, unlicensed crypto-to-wire exchange, luxury spending and mansion rentals funded by stolen assets, straw owner concealment for homes and vehicles, bulk cash shipment concealed in clothing or stuffed animals, post-arrest evidence destruction directed by enterprise members, off-duty law enforcement tip-off alleged."
      }
    },
